               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1200" notAfter="1300">1200-1300</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">Post-Aksumite potsherds (dating between 700/800 and 1200/1300 A.D.), remains of early medieval structures have been recorded at the site. According to local tradition, the church was founded by <persName ref="PRS7594Noah">Noah</persName> (? or a certain local Noy ?).
                     The name of the area, <placeName ref="LOC7254AddiQanay">ʿĀddi Qanay</placeName>,  is said to have been derived from "Noy" (<persName ref="PRS7594Noah">Noah</persName>; <quote xml:lang="gez">ʿĀddi daqqi Noy</quote>).</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Gatar. &#xD;
                     Burial places are located under the overhanging rock, along the river <placeName ref="LOC1451Angar">ʾAngār</placeName>. The old deserted church rock-churcn stands behind the recently built one.&#xD;
                     Two ruined structures standing closer to the entrance into the gorge are said to be churches of "<persName ref="PRS10429Yohanni" type="tabot">ʾabbā Yoḥanni</persName>" and "<persName ref="PRS1257Aboli" type="tabot">ʾabbā ʾAboli</persName>" (?).     &#xD;
</ab>
                  <ab type="description">
                     <figure>
                        <graphic url="Sites/MGM.tif">
                           <desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</desc>
                        </graphic>
                     </figure>19 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm001">MGM-001</ref> “Miracles of Jesus”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm002">MGM-002</ref> “Homily of st. Michael; Miracles of St. Michal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm003">MGM-003</ref> “Collection of Homilies”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm004">MGM-004</ref> “Pauline Epistles; Acts of the Apostles; Catholic Epistles; Apocalipse of John”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm005">MGM-005</ref> “Synaxarion (The first half of the years)”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm006">MGM-006</ref> “Miracles of Mary”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm007">MGM-007</ref> “Vita of the Apostles”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm008">MGM-008</ref> “Miracles of Jesus ”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm009">MGM-009</ref> “Synaxarion (The second half of the year)”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm010">MGM-010</ref> “Praise of Mary; Collection; Images of the Praise; A Part of Dǝggwa”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm011">MGM-011</ref> “Prayer of Incense; Missal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm012">MGM-012</ref> “Vita of Libanos Miracles of Libanos”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm013">MGM-013</ref> “Vita of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus; Miracles of Gäbrä  Mänfäs Qǝddus”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm014">MGM-014</ref> “Vita of Gäbrä Mänfäs Qǝddus; Miracles of Gäbrä  Mänfäs Qǝddus”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm015">MGM-015</ref> “The Book of the Baptismal Rite”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm016">MGM-016</ref> “Vita of ʾArägawi”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmgm017">MGM-017</ref> “The Book of the Funeral Rite”; MGM-leaves 1 (18) Fragments of different manuscripts; MGM-leaves 2 (19) Fragments of different manuscripts.</ab>

